sales_opportunities.title: Northwest Metaphysical Market (NWMM)
sales_opportunities.description:
Northwest Metaphysical Market (NWMM) is an outdoor artisan and spiritual marketplace held in the heart of Downtown Tacoma on Broadway between S 9th St & S 11th St, directly across from Historic Antique Row! This curated event brings together metaphysical makers, holistic practitioners, intuitive readers, and an eclectic community of local artisans for a day of meaningful connection, healing, and unique shopping experiences.

Guests can explore a wide range of offerings, including crystals, handcrafted goods, wellness products, altar tools, jewelry, tarot/oracle readings, energy work, and art of all kinds. The market is FREE to the public and is open from 11:00 AM to 5:00 PM, making it a welcoming and accessible event for all ages.

Parking & Other Information:

Visitors may utilize nearby paid street parking, surrounding garages, and public parking lots throughout the downtown area. Street parking is typically free on Sundays, and most locations are within a short walking distance of the market.

The market is fully outdoors—guests are encouraged to dress for the weather.

Service animals are always welcome; pets should remain leashed at all times.

Respectful behavior toward vendors, guests, and spiritual practices is mandatory.

Join us and experience a magical blend of creativity, spirituality, and community in one of Tacoma’s most historic districts! ✨
sales_opportunities.address: S 9th St & Broadway, Tacoma, Washington 98402, United States

sales_opportunities.title: Tacoma Sunday Market March 1
sales_opportunities.description:
Thank you for you interest in vending at the Tacoma Sunday Market. This is a juried flea market and all applications will be reviewed.  All vending spaces are 10x10 and in a covered parking garage located at 923 Commerce St, Tacoma, WA 98402. Vehicle height restricted to 7'4" and under. Vehicles taller than 7'4" must load in/out via the street.  Form of payment provided with application will only be charged if and when application is approved. 

About the event
First Sunday's of the month are for flea marketing at the Tacoma Sunday Market! Shop for vintage clothing, collectibles, vintage furniture, jewelry, sneakers, handmade goods, flowers, and more! Grab a bite and drink from the food trucks and enjoy the DJs. Be sure to take cute free photos at the selfie stations throughout the market. Free! Family friendly! Friendly Fur babies are always welcome! Tons of free parking!

opportunity_reviews.text: Very nice little place and we'll maintained. Went there for the 7th annual Turkey Trot. Lots of fun.
Beautiful space to rent, comes with an indoor kitchen and bathrooms. Air-conditioned, michelle referred me to Line Roy for reservations and it was a pleasant experience. Thank you

I love this town! Had a blast at the Yelm Farmers Market here which is every Saturday through the summer from 10am-3pm. Such YUMMY homemade, local food and Mari's veggies from her farm are always TOP NOTCH, organic and reasonably priced. Oh! And, FYI, a new water feature for the kids is going in on the playground right there and will be opening in a few weeks so go check it out!

The Yelm Community Center is great for a family get together or a party. The facility is large and clean. You're able to see the kiddos play on the playground and can open the big glass doors up to the outside.    We will definitely be back.
Yelm is BY FAR the best community in WA

A good farmers market with a broad variety of produce (peppers, dried Chiles like chipotle, heirloom tomatoes, apples, mushrooms). You can also find honey, bread, apple cider, hot sauces, meat, cheese, sandwiches, and pizza.

I love shopping at this farmer's market on Saturday morning. There is an abundance of fresh fruit and vegetables.
The vendors are friendly, and the prices are good enough. Big difference in quality compared to grocery stores. We love all the farmers' produce. However, the price for flowers is way too much for their quality, my bouquet died after 3 days.

They have free parking for an hour!

This market is a happy place because it is full of artisans with great products.  Beautiful fruits and vegetables, pasture raised meats, and good food.  A wonderful place to spend a Saturday morning.  The quintessential farmers market.
We like this market! We come here almost every weekend. The favorite vendor is the cider farm: Rockridge Orchards, they just have the best cider and apple juice. Highly recommend it!

Fresh produce and fruits, great bakery’s and local businesses featuring custom products like teas, kombucha, honeys and so much more. Runs all year, but parking can be tricky so be ready to be patient
Tha Aguilar vegetable stand is beautiful. The owners are so nice and helpful. Do not miss this one!

I loved the yummy ice cream!! It was all so tasty! I enjoyed just about everything. All were very kind and sweet. There were many stands all quite different. I got a delicious buttermilk & honey ice cream. An amazing experience!

Very cool market, there were a few that stood out, the man selling local honey was very kind and informative. The oysters and mussels were delicious. And there's a woman who sells cbd topical creams and they WORKED like amazingly good.
Lots to look at and see. They had small plants, hot sauce, cherrys, and apples, and vegetables
Awesome setup with several cool shops. Reasonable prices and a nice festive environment.

I really love the variety of vendors this farmers market has throughout the season and week to week. It always has me coming back and wondering what new products they’ll have. I just wish they extended their season through October like the Redmond farmers market.
Very cute market with a Wine Alley behind it. A nice place to spend an afternoon.
I'm a musician who plays this market, and it is my favorite!  The vendors are just lovely and so varied, the patrons are kind and gracious and the market manager amazing!
Very nice place, good selection, could use a couple of park benches or something to sit on
A fun place to find freash flowers, vegetables, pasteries and tastings of coffee. Meet up with old friends

Get out here! ...next week. 10-4. Lots of great vendors, garage market is great in and of itself! Lots of clothes booths, unique crafts, artisans, and superior food trucks! Hey on the road early, whether you're in Tacoma, Everett, or Issaquah,Il it's worth the drive ...especially as the weekend market season winds down.

Great local farmers market.  Lots of variety with rotating vendors.  You never know what you will discover, but it is a fun spot on a summer Thursday afternoon and I’m sure you’ll find something you would like.
I loved the diversity of the food stalls! Got the banh khot from Elotador and they were so good and freshly made, highly recommend!
